  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Solutions Design Manager (Security Systems)",
  "description": "<p>Monday - Friday<br />9 AM - 6 PM<br />Location: Central <br />Benefits: Medical Insurance Coverage, Transport Allowances, AWS + VB<br /><br />We are representing a well-established <strong>security systems integrator</strong> in Singapore seeking an experienced <strong>Solutions Design Manager</strong> to lead technical solutioning for large-scale security projects and tenders.</p><p>This is a senior role bridging <strong>commercial strategy and engineering excellence</strong>, responsible for shaping integrated security solutions across CCTV, Access Control, Intrusion Systems, and AI-driven analytics.</p><h3>Key Responsibilities</h3><ul><li><p>Lead end-to-end <strong>solution design for major security bids</strong>, translating complex client requirements into scalable, cost-effective architectures.</p></li><li><p>Act as the <strong>technical authority</strong> for electronic security solutions, evaluating platforms, vendors, and emerging technologies.</p></li><li><p>Drive <strong>PoC testing, product validation, and solution innovation</strong> to maintain market competitiveness.</p></li><li><p>Partner with commercial and procurement teams to optimise <strong>BOM and total cost of ownership</strong>.</p></li><li><p>Lead and mentor a specialised solutions engineering team, including remote team members.</p></li><li><p>Work closely with senior leadership to align solution design with the company’s long-term technology roadmap.</p></li></ul><h3>Requirements</h3><ul><li><p>4+ years in the electronic security industry, with 3+ years in a senior design or leadership role within a systems integrator environment.</p></li><li><p>Strong expertise in enterprise security systems (VMS, ACS, biometrics, intrusion, unified platforms).</p></li><li><p>Proven leadership and stakeholder management skills.</p></li><li><p>Singapore-based with immediate or short notice availability.</p></li><li><p>Confident communicator, able to engage senior executives and public-sector stakeholders.</p></li></ul><h3>Preferred</h3><ul><li><p>CPP / PSP / CCNA or equivalent certifications</p></li><li><p>Lead-level certifications in Genetec, Lenel, AMAG, or similar platforms<br /></p><p>Interested candidates, please WhatsApp me at 8779 6100 or send in your resume to willie.goh@swiftsearchglobal.com</p><p>We regret to inform you that only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</p><p>Willie Goh | EA Reg No: R2197853</p><p>Swift Search Global Pte Ltd | EA No: 18C9495</p></li></ul>",
